  "prompt": "How do you invert your selection in Photoshop?",
  "response": "In Adobe Photoshop, there are several ways to invert a selection:\n\n1. Keyboard Shortcut Method:\n\u2022 Press Ctrl+Shift+I (Windows)\n\u2022 Press Command+Shift+I (Mac)\n\n2. Menu Method:\n\u2022 Go to Select > Inverse\n\n3. Using the Select Menu:\n\u2022 Click Select in the top menu\n\u2022 Choose \"Inverse\" from the dropdown menu\n\nAll of these methods will swap your current selection, selecting everything that was previously unselected and deselecting the original selection.",
